The Exchange is subject to:
the following provisions of the State Finance and Procurement Article:
Title 12, Subtitle 4 (Policies and Procedures for Exempt Units); and
Title 14, Subtitle 3 (Minority Business Participation);
the following provisions of the State Government Article:
Title 10, Subtitle 1 (Governmental Procedures);
Title 10, Subtitle 5 (Meetings);
Title 10, Subtitle 6, Part III (Access to Public Records);
Title 12 (Immunity and Liability); and
Title 15 (Public Ethics); and
Title 5, Subtitle 3 of the State Personnel and Pensions Article.

The Exchange is not subject to:
taxation by the State or local government;
Division II of the State Finance and Procurement Article, except as provided in subsection (a)(1) of this section;
Title 10 of the State Government Article, except as provided in subsection (a)(2)(i), (ii), and (iii) of this section; or
Division I of the State Personnel and Pensions Article, except as provided in subsection (a)(3) of this section and elsewhere in this title.
